<Document>
<name>Beartooth Highway</name>
<description><![CDATA[<h2>Beartooth Highway</h2><p><i>Montana / Wyoming, USA · US-212, Red Lodge to Cooke City</i></p><p><b>Charles Kuralt called it 'the most beautiful drive in America.' Switchbacks to a 3,337 m alpine plateau.</b></p><table style='font-family:sans-serif'><tr><td><b>Approx. length:</b></td><td>76 km (47 mi)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Drive time:</b></td><td>3–4 hrs</td></tr><tr><td><b>Best season:</b></td><td>Late June–mid September; closed roughly Oct–May</td></tr><tr><td><b>Watch out for:</b></td><td>Snow possible in July; no services for 100 km between Red Lodge and Cooke City; high altitude; weather changes in minutes</td></tr><tr><td><b>Track points:</b></td><td>220</td></tr></table><hr><p>Completed in 1936 specifically to give Yellowstone a northeast entrance from Red Lodge. The road climbs 1,500 m in switchbacks past wildflower meadows that don't melt out until July. Above 3,000 m you're on a treeless plateau that resembles the Tibetan steppe — pikas, marmots, bighorn sheep, occasional grizzly. The summit at 3,337 m is the third-highest paved highway in the United States. There is no fuel or food between Red Lodge and Cooke City; fill up before you start.</p><h3>Scenic points marked on this route:</h3><ul><li><b>Rock Creek Vista</b> — First major overlook (2,743 m). Glacial U-valley below; switchbacks ahead. Boardwalk to the edge — accessible.</li><li><b>Beartooth Pass summit</b> — 3,337 m. Plant life here is identical to the Arctic — willows that take 50 years to grow as tall as your boot.</li><li><b>Beartooth Lake</b> — Striking turquoise water against the iron-red Beartooth Butte. Picnic area; grizzly country.</li><li><b>Pilot–Index Peaks viewpoint</b> — These twin volcanic spires are perhaps the most photographed mountains in northern Wyoming. Best light: late afternoon.</li><li><b>Crazy Creek Falls</b> — Tumbling 12 m cascade right beside the road. Picnic spot; 1.5 km trail along the creek.</li></ul><hr><p><i>Track geometry is interpolated between named waypoints — use a routing service to snap to actual road for navigation. Waypoints, scenic POIs, and notes are reliable.</i></p>]]></description>
